At least, two people were yesterday killed in the multiple pipeline fire that occurred at Fagba and Ekoro road area of the state. Confirming the fire outbreak, the director general/ Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA). Dr. Oke-Osanyintolu said that the agency responded immediately they were alerted. As at the time of filling this report, residents of Abule Egba area of Lagos State were jittery as the pipeline explosion fire raged unabated. The explosion was said to have occurred from a ruptured pipeline caused by activities of vandals around the area. Though the extent of damage and destructions in the area was yet to be ascertained, the fire was still raging as at the time of filing this report. LASEMA investigation revealed that the inferno was as a result of pipeline vandalism. “Two adult male died; eleven trucks laden with 40feet containers were destroyed while about seven buildings have so far been razed down by the inferno.”